"Damn, I failed again huh" - I thought to myself. Since I have reached my 10th pull (cause I did 6 singles beforehand), the 2x summon button is now the button that might bring happiness or despair to me. Before pressing, I used the recording option in phone just to capture the moment of either my happiest moment, or the greatest downfall. I pressed the button and the confirmation firmly, with 5 seconds of holding time. Wait, was that a LOADING after a CONNECTING? This might mean that I'm getting a new unit. I felt a small lag, with 3 rings and no signs of gold or rainbow orbs. And then a golden card appeared before me. A GOLDEN RIDER card. "Pls dont be a spook, I beg you" - words that I chanted as my heart pounded so hard. The card's identity is the servant I dreamt of getting for months - R E I N E S .  Well, since it was a 2 summon, I also got another William Tell. But ignore that. I got her in my last 3 sq. If you reached this far, then may you be blessed in your rolls.

After miserably failing her banner half year ago, I have sworn to do everything in order to get her in her next banner.
With her surprise banner in Thanksgiving event, I was determined to do multi pulls in order to get her. But sadly, I failed to get her.
But then I realized, thanks to my last multi, I got Rama - the final piece in order to do the 100 interludes for the 10 sq.
Having 1 sq left, I grinded all the mats and exp cards just to get Rama into 3rd Ascension and Bond 5 just to unlock his interlude.
Alas, I have obtained a total of 11 sq (1 from his interlude and 10 from 100 interludes completed). A total of 12 sq is now in my hands.
With these spare quartz, I put all of my faith in doing the 4 singles. It was only a few hours until her rate-up leaves and this would be my last hope.
1st pull - a 3* CE. No biggies, I still have 3 more. 2nd pull - William Tell (a 3* servant). Ok, I'm starting to lose hope.
3rd pull - Bronze Link Manipulator 3* CE. Fuck. *Continuation above*
